<font color="#FF0000">MAYA LIN &amp; THE VIETNAMMEMORIAL</font><br>
<tt>Thu May  1 12:52:23 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I enjoyed the program that aired that showed in detail about vetnam veterens, their memorial and Maya Lin. The history of this was touching and an eye opener.                         I'm in my early 30's so I know little about the war itself; just what they told us in school and TV. The few people that I know that were involved with this war or others do not talk or express feelings, their oppinions on them.           The way Maya Lin has broke through barriors of racual,gender discrimination in her life is inspiring to others and to our children for Maya Lin is an role model to them. I enjoy her work and the fact that she's doing what she's whated to do and is making an statement.
